race.comment: LAVANDULA (8) won a 56 by 4L at Ballarat first-up and seeks the hat-trick further improved. Has been kept up to the mark with a placed jumpout at Geelong and maps for the run of the race. She's promising and can take the next step. ETERNAL DARKNESS (4) is another heading in the right direction. Just missed here first up following knee surgery, and will be sharper with that under the belt. He's been kept on the fresh side and using the low barrier will get every chance. GRAND INTENTION (14) resumes and has a chance if presented forward. She's quick and was a big Ballarat Maiden winner two back. Has had throat surgery since last seen, but has been sharp in her jumpouts.
